nother country. <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> officials say the activists will not be forced to leave the consulate, despite a worldwide <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> policy of not formally granting asylum in diplomatic offices. <LOCATION> South </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Africa </LOCATION> would need <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> permission to enter the premises. Under apartheid, <LOCATION> South </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Africa </LOCATION>'s 26 million blacks have no vote in national affairs. The 5 million whites control the economy and maintain separate districts, schools and health services.
