<BYLINE>By SERGEI SHARGARODSKY</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>JERUSALEM (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The army ordered 180,000 Palestinian refugees to stay in their homes in the occupied <LOCATION> Gaza </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Strip </LOCATION> today in anticipation of a general strike called by Moslem fundamentalists and PLO-linked underground leaders. In a pre-dawn firefight in south <LOCATION> Lebanon </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Israeli </LOCATION> troops killed three guerrillas without suffering casualties, the army said. Documents found on the bodies showed the guerrillas belonged to <PERSON> Yasser </PERSON> <PERSON> Arafat </PERSON>'s Fatah branch of the <ORGANIZATION> PLO </ORGANIZATION>, <ORGANIZATION> Israel </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> radio </ORGANIZATION> said. In <LOCATION> Gaza </LOCATION>, the round-the-clock curfew was imposed indefinitely on the Shati, Jabaliya, Nusseirat, Bureij, Maghazi and <PERSON> Khan </PERSON> <PERSON> Yunis </PERSON> camps, the army and <PERSON> Arab </PERSON> reports said. It came after a violent clash at the camp Thursday night in which 20 Palestinians attacked <LOCATION> Israeli </LOCATION> soldiers with firebombs, iron chains and clubs, the army said. Troops opened fire, wounding two Palestinians, the army said. Also today, peace crusader <PERSON> Abie </PERSON> <PERSON> Nathan </PERSON> was summoned before police in the <LOCATION> Tel </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Aviv </LOCATION> suburb of <ORGANIZATION> Petah </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Tikva </ORGANIZATION> for an investigation into his meeting with <ORGANIZATION> Palestine </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Liberation </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Organization </ORGANIZATION> chief <PERSON> Yasser </PERSON> <PERSON> Arafat </PERSON> in <LOCATION> Tunis </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Tunisia </LOCATION>, on Tuesday. <PERSON> Nathan </PERSON> faces up to three years in jail for breaking an <LOCATION> Israeli </LOCATION> law banning contacts with terrorist groups. <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION> views the <ORGANIZATION> PLO </ORGANIZATION> as a terrorist group. Defense Minister <PERSON>