<HEAD>Sinkhole Believed To Be Cause Of Derailment</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JACKSONVILLE, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A sinkhole that opened up beneath a stretch of railroad track caused 27 cars of a freight train to derail, <ORGANIZATION> CSX </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Transportation </ORGANIZATION> officials said Friday. `` The hole is the cause of the accident, there is no doubt about that. It's as if a bridge fell or a tunnel collapsed. It's obvious the whole track dropped fix to six feet. But we do n't know why,'' <ORGANIZATION> CSX </ORGANIZATION> spokesman <PERSON> Lloyd </PERSON> <PERSON> Lewis </PERSON> said. `` The whole crossing where that track is contained is gone,'' he said. Another <ORGANIZATION> CSX </ORGANIZATION> spokesman, <PERSON> Lindsay </PERSON> <PERSON> Leckie </PERSON>, said a depression, about 100 feet long, 10 feet wide and 5 feet deep, formed under the tracks as the train rolled along early Thursday. `` There was apparently some water intrusion under the roadbed which caused the track structure to collapse. The key question is what caused this intrusion,'' <PERSON> Leckie </PERSON> said. He said the appearance of the hole was `` sudden, unobservable and undetectable,'' adding that four locomotives and eight cars passed over it before the derailment and other trains had used the tracks an hour earlier. Tanker cars damaged in the derailment spewed noxious fumes into the air. Two <ORGANIZATION> Florida </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Highway </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Patrol </ORGANIZATION> troopers were hospitalized for respiratory problems after inhaling potassium hydroxide, and several other officers and railroad workers were treated for respiratory problems. The derailment forced the closing of five major intersections and 45 nearby businesses. Four intersections and the businesses reopened Friday.
